23. Program to Implement Signal (Interrupt) Handling in C++**

Aim:

To implement *signal (interrupt) handling* using the signal() function in C++.

Algorithm:

1. Include <csignal> and <iostream>.
2. Define a signal handler function.
3. Register the handler using signal(SIGINT, handler).
4. Run an infinite loop to test the interrupt (Ctrl+C).

Program:

#include <iostream>
#include <csignal>
#include <unistd.h>
using namespace std;

void signalHandler(int signum) {
    cout << "\nInterrupt signal (" << signum << ") received.\n";
    exit(signum);
}

int main() {
    signal(SIGINT, signalHandler);
    while (1) {
        cout << "Running... Press Ctrl+C to stop.\n";
        sleep(2);
    }
    return 0;
}


Output:


Running... Press Ctrl+C to stop.
^C
Interrupt signal (2) received.


Result:

Successfully implemented *signal handling* in C++.
